[thinking] **Evaluating API features**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I think root replacement is an interesting test, but I'm wondering if the API supports patch capabilities at the document root. It seems like existing non-object merge patches replace the entire document, while JSON Patch is newer and also works similarly. I need to avoid duplicating whole document replacements since it appears that the current non-object merge patch might cover some merging logic. Plus, it raises questions about JsonMergePatch serialization of non-objects since there seems to be no existing serialization for that. Maybe I should check if the library includes JsonMergePatch and look into the differences.
